  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "HR Executive (Payroll & Business Partner)",
  "description": "<p><strong>❗Current work location at Shun Li Industrial Complex and moving to Senoko Way in Q2 2026❗</strong><br /></p><p><strong>Payroll Management</strong></p><ul><li>Manage end-to-end payroll processing of approximately 700 employees accurately and on time</li><li>Ensure compliance with statutory requirements (tax, CPF, labor laws, etc.)</li><li>Maintain payroll records, employee data, and confidential information</li><li>Handle payroll queries and resolve discrepancies</li><li>Coordinate with finance and external vendors (if applicable)</li></ul><p><strong>HR Business Partnering</strong></p><ul><li>Act as a trusted HR partner to assigned departments</li><li>Support managers with employee relations, performance management, and workforce planning</li><li>Provide guidance on HR policies, procedures, and best practices</li><li>Assist in employee engagement and retention initiatives</li><li>Support organizational change and HR projects as needed</li></ul><p><strong>HR Operations</strong></p><ul><li>Support onboarding, offboarding, and employee lifecycle activities</li><li>Maintain HR documentation and reports</li><li>Ensure HR processes are efficient and compliant with company policies</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p><ul><li>Diploma in Human Resources, Business Administration, or related field</li><li>3 years of experience in HR, with strong exposure to payroll processing</li><li>Solid understanding of labor laws and statutory compliance</li><li>Experience in an HR Business Partner or advisory role is an advantage</li><li>Strong attention to detail and high level of confidentiality</li><li>Good communication and stakeholder management skills</li><li>Proficiency in HRIS, payroll systems, and MS Excel</li></ul></p>",
